  "pr_number": 6030,
  "issue_number": 4078,
  "issue_title": "bug: WS stops working on iOS safari after some time and no reconnect happens",
  "issue_body": "### Provide environment information\r\n\r\n```\r\n  System:\r\n    OS: macOS 13.0\r\n    CPU: (10) arm64 Apple M1 Max\r\n    Memory: 7.35 GB / 32.00 GB\r\n    Shell: 5.8.1 - /bin/zsh\r\n  Binaries:\r\n    Node: 16.16.0 - ~/.asdf/installs/nodejs/16.16.0/bin/node\r\n    Yarn: 1.22.19 - ~/.asdf/installs/nodejs/16.16.0/.npm/bin/yarn\r\n    npm: 8.11.0 - ~/.asdf/plugins/nodejs/shims/npm\r\n    Watchman: 2023.01.23.00 - /opt/homebrew/bin/watchman\r\n  Browsers:\r\n    Chrome: 111.0.5563.110\r\n    Firefox: 109.0.1\r\n    Safari: 16.1\r\n    Safari Technology Preview: 16.4\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nAfter some time when tab is suspended on iOS safari, WS stops working on iOS safari. WebSocket doesn't emit `close` event, and it just hangs. No reconnect happen\r\n\r\n### To reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Open site with iOS Safari\r\n2. Switch to other apps\r\n3. Wait ~3-5 min\r\n4. Return to safari browser\r\n5. WS stops working, no reconnect happens\r\n\r\nI also checked the \"network\" tab. The connection looks like is not closed, but not events are emitting.\r\n\r\n### Additional information\r\n\r\nI found a dirty workaround:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\ndocument.addEventListener(\"visibilitychange\", () => {\r\n  // Let's reconnect on visibility change,\r\n  // Cause, for example, iOS safari connection may hang\r\n  if (document.visibilityState === \"visible\") {\r\n    wsClient.getConnection().dispatchEvent(new CloseEvent(\"close\"));\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd, an interesting thing, is that I need to make `wsClient.getConnection().dispatchEvent(new CloseEvent(\"close\"))`. If I do just `wsClient.close()` \u2014 nothing happens. I think `close` event just not emitting when WebSocket is hanged.\r\n\r\nI found the same issue at `graphql-ws`, so it may help https://github.com/enisdenjo/graphql-ws/discussions/290 . They recommend using this solution \u2014 https://the-guild.dev/graphql/ws/recipes#client-usage-with-abrupt-termination-on-pong-timeout\r\n\r\n<sub>[TRP-16](https://linear.app/trpc/issue/TRP-16/bug-ws-stops-working-on-ios-safari-after-some-time-and-no-reconnect)</sub>",
